line_1: A Muse expiring, who with earliest voice,
line_2: Made kings and queens, and beauty's charms her choice,

line_1: Now on her death bed, the last homage pays,
line_2: O Queen, to thee; accept her dying lays.

line_1: O Queen, to thee; accept her dying lays.
line_2: Now on her death bed, the last homage pays,

line_1: So at th' approach of death the cygnet tries
line_2: To warble one note more, and singing dies.

line_1: To warble one note more, and singing dies.
line_2: So at th' approach of death the cygnet tries

line_1: Hail mighty Queen, whose powerful smiles alone
line_2: Command obedience and secure the throne.

line_1: Command obedience and secure the throne.
line_2: Hail mighty Queen, whose powerful smiles alone
Had puzzled Loyalty for half an age:

line_1: Had puzzled Loyalty for half an age:
Conqu'ring our hearts you end the long dispute;
line_2: All who have eyes confess you absolute;

line_1: All who have eyes confess you absolute;
line_2: Conqu'ring our hearts you end the long dispute;

line_1: To Tory doctrines even Whigs resign,
line_2: And in your person own the right divine.

line_1: And in your person own the right divine.
line_2: To Tory doctrines even Whigs resign,

line_1: Thus sung the Muse, in her last moments fir'd
line_2: With CAROLINA'S praise, and then expir'd.
